\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 18. Owlbear's lair : Owlbear, treasure
\f1\b0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\i\fs26 \cf0 A huge birds nest of branches, fur, feathers and leaves is the most outwardly obvious thing in the chamber. It takes up much of the north west corner, and although empty of life you can see golden reflections glittering in and around the nest. Painted on the walls are scenes of strange dwarf-like figures stood around a black tower in what appears to be communion.
\f1\i0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The Owlbear is almost always found here (a 1 in 20 chance otherwise) and will have sensed the approach of the party unless they have managed to travel perfectly quietly. It lurks hidden in the south west corner when it hears someone approaching, otherwise it maybe asleep on it's nest. It will try and surprise anyone entering and can be extremely quiet after all it's years of hunting these passages. It should be noted again that the Owlbear maybe be too challenging a monster for the players when they first encounter it, but it moves relatively slowly and can be fled from. It makes for a fearsome protagonist throughout the level, seeking out the adventurers and you might, if you wish, use it to herd them into areas you particularly want them to experience.
\f1\fs24 \
